               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#add-summary">
                     1 copy of Sharaf Namah by Bidlīsī, Sharaf Khān, b. 1543
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="RAS_Persian_158-item1">
                     <author key="person_81963927" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/81963927/">
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Bidlīsī, Sharaf Khān, b. 1543</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar">شرف الدين البتليسي</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_5746">Sharaf Namah.</title>
                     <note>Folio 1, recto: Presented by Sir John Malcolm May 19. 1827 On cream-coloured European paper. Ardalani's addition occupies ff34-40 of the MS, following Sharaf Khan's passage on the Ardalan chiefs. It is written on blue watermarked paper, probably Russian and has a colophon dated Rajab 1225. At the top of f34a is a note, presumably in the hand of John Malcolm: Sup[p]lement sent to me by the Waly of Ardalan. Under the colophon, also presumably by Malcolm: Finis. A history of the Kurds. Misbound into this MS is a supplement by Muhammad Ibrahim b, Mulla Muhammad Husain Ardalani, briefly giving the history of the Kurdish governors of Ardalan up to 1225. See notes. Headings and punctuation in red.</note>
                     <incipit>Wa 'alaihi tawakkaltu innahu malikun karimun (Differs from the incipit given in Rieu.)</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>Storey, i, pp. 366-9.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Rieu, i, p 208-9.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Morley gives a very detailed description.</bibl>
                        <bibl>(Storey lists no other copy of Ardalani's continuation.)</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
